definition: (prefix indicating ordinal number, e.g. first, number two etc)/order/(old) rank in the imperial examinations/mansion/(literary) but/just

sentences.english: China was second with 32, four behind the United States.
sentences.chinese: 中國有32枚，比美國少4枚，排在第二位。

sentences.english: Breast cancer is the second leading cause of cancer-related deaths among American women.
sentences.chinese: 乳腺癌是美國婦女癌症相關死因中列於第二位。

sentences.english: The second one is novelist Mme Nothomb.
sentences.chinese: 第二位是著名女作家諾冬。

sentences.english: The incidence of olfactory neuroblastoma was the second common ocular malignant tumor.

sentences.english: To get there, Google needs to drink even more of the social Kool-Aid than it has.

sentences.english: From 1980 to 1984, it was the second leading cause of death .

sentences.english: Nigeria has a score of 3.5, the second-lowest.

sentences.english: NBC and Fox were neck-and-neck for second place.

sentences.english: Number two on the list is Karnak temple that is situated neat Luxor, Egypt.

sentences.english: Today, many advertising slogans later, it's still No. 2.

sentences.english: Based on the absolute differences, the relevancy degree of fisheermen's wage income is at the second place.

sentences.english: The second woman also recorded her statement before she died.
sentences.chinese: 第二位婦女也在臨死前錄下了證詞。

sentences.english: All of the LeBron scheming is simply positioning for a place in line. The second place in line. Period.

sentences.english: In the second place, company passed to the three-layered structure disk.

sentences.english: He come second in the contest for deputy leader.

sentences.english: Brown was the second offensive lineman chosen in the draft.
sentences.chinese: 布朗是選秀中被選中的第二位進攻內鋒。
